HE BASICALLY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY, DURING THE DAY RICHARD WOULD HAVE TO BE QUIET.
BUT AFTER SCHOOL WAS OUT AND EVERYBODY LEFT.
RICHARD WAS ABLE TO SCREAM AND HOLLER, AND RUN THROUGH THE LIBRARY.
HE WOULD STAY UP AND READ BOOKS UNTIL 3 A.
NO ONE IN HIS FAMILY GRADUATED FROM SCHOOL OR COLLEGE.
RICHARD WAS THE FIRST TO GRADUATE FROM COLLEGE.
AND HE RECEIVED A JOB AS A PROFESSOR AND HIS DAD WAS PROUD.

HE REALLY DIDN'T HAVE MANY OR ANY FRIENDS AT ALL.
THIS PARTICULAR STORY WAS BASED IN THE 1940'S, WITH A LITTLE BOY NAME RICHARD CLARK.
HIS DAD BECAME THE CUSTODIAN OF THE A LIBRARY, KNOWN AS THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
RICHARD LOVE TO READ, HE WOULD LIVE IN THE LIBRARY, AND STAY UP READING BOOKS UNTIL 3 AM IN THE MORNING.
RICHARD WAS POOR, AND WAS ASHAMED OF BRINGING HIS FRIENDS TO HIS HOUSE.
HE LATER GREW UP, AND BECAME THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE FROM COLLEGE.
RICHARD BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE, AND HIS FATHER WAS PROUD, BUT QUIET.
RICHARD LIVED WITH HIS MOTHER AND FATHER.
HIS FATHER WAS KNOWN FOR CLEANING THE TOP OF THE SHELVES AT THE LIBRARY.
